      %h3.text-center What is Matrix?
      %p Matrix is an open specification for an online communication protocol. It includes all the features you'd expect from a modern chat platform including instant messaging, group chats, audio and video calls, searchable message history, synchronization across all your devices, and end-to-end encryption. Matrix is federated, so no single company controls the system or your data. You can use an existing server you trust or run your own, and the servers synchronize messages seamlessly. Learn more in the <a href="/docs/matrix/">Introduction to Matrix</a>.

  .row
